ABOUT HEALTHIX
Largest Public HIE in the Nation
More than
28,000,000
patients
Healthix contains data from healthcare organizations throughout
New York City and Long Island. Healthix uses sophisticated software to
reconcile data of over 87.5 million provider Medical Record Numbers
(MRNs) to create composite profiles of over 28.6 million patients.
Over 900 health care organizations at more
than 6,100 sites across
New York City and Long Island participate in
Healthix.
Supplies secure data to
improve healthcare quality,
efficiency and effectiveness
Provides a range of clinical
information
in real-time
Facilitates care coordination
Healthix is the largest public
Health Information Exchange (HIE)
in the United States

Barriers and Challenges
Three primary challenges:
1. Developing the business case
Seeking matching accuracy
Leveraging referential patient demographic data improves the matching process
Cost savings
2. Ensuring security and privacy
Gaining buy-in from key stakeholders
Meeting required security standards e.g. HITRUST
3. Selecting a vendor
Rapid Scalability
Backlog of over 10M patient linkages that needed to be processed
Daily maintenance of messages > 10,000 new potential patient linkages
Strong partnership and support
Mission alignment
BENEFITS OF LEVERAGING
A CLOUD-BASED EMPI
Results Post Implementation
The final results have been very positive for Healthix:
6% (1.74 million) reduction of unique patient counts
Resulted from a better matching process
More clinical records are now available for a patient
A cost savings of 28% total of ownership over 3 years
Simplified infrastructure for customer (Hardware & Software Upgrades)
Service improvements (Scalability, High Availability & Disaster Recovery)
Maintain security level required for organization (HITRUST, etc..)
Avoid one time implementation costs
Facility MRNs per EID increased
+ 22% from Oct 2016 to Feb 2017
+ 31% from Oct 2016 to Sep 2017
Healthix continues to see an increase in:
Number of MRNs per EID (3.06 MRNs
per Identity for Dec 2018)
Slower increase in EIDs as MRN
counts grow:
87.5M MRNs
28.6M EIDs

HEALTHIX PHILOSOPHY
ON MOVING ENTERPRISE
SOFTWARE TO CLOUD
What works for your organization?
Finding the balance:
What is your type of business (services, product development)?
Staffing situation?
Does your staff have the skill sets required?
What is your goal and endgame?
Does it make financial sense to move to the cloud?
Do you have a business continuity plan?
Recommendations
Conduct a significant amount of due diligence when seeking cloud-based solutions for
any enterprisewide technologies
Make your own calculations on cost and resource savings
Create your own business case
Does the decision best support your business?
